data.name: textBox2.Text
data.value: Unplug the SMART Board USB cable going to your computer. This cable has a brick/power adapter partway down the cable that says SMART on it. Plug the USB cable back into a USB port that is not blue and that does not have "SS" marked beside the port.

data.name: textBox5.Text
data.value: Look to see if the light on the bottom right-hand corner of your SMART board is red or green. If it is green, move on to the next step. If it is red or flashing, unplug your SMART board power cable from the wall and plug it back in.
